## Frame.dev Specific Guidelines

### Theme System
Frame Codex supports 8 themes:
- `light`, `dark` (standard)
- `sepia-light`, `sepia-dark` (vintage/book)
- `terminal-light`, `terminal-dark` (CRT/retro)
- `oceanic-light`, `oceanic-dark` (ocean-inspired)

All colors MUST use CSS variables from the theme system.

### OpenStrand Schema
- **Fabric**: The entire knowledge repository
- **Weave**: Top-level knowledge universe (e.g., weaves/technology/)
- **Loom**: Subdirectory/module within a weave
- **Strand**: Atomic knowledge unit (markdown file or folder with strand.yml)

### Component Conventions
- Use Framer Motion for animations
- Tailwind CSS with custom design tokens
- Lucide React for icons
- Support all 8 themes in every component
- Mobile-first responsive design
- 44px minimum touch targets

### File Structure
```
apps/frame.dev/
  components/codex/      # Core Codex components
    ui/                  # Reusable UI components
    hooks/               # Custom React hooks
    tree/                # Tree navigation components
  app/codex/             # Next.js pages
  lib/codex/             # Utilities, data, helpers
  styles/                # Global styles, theme CSS
  types/                 # TypeScript definitions
```

